The paper deals with game theory and network pricing, which are both topics covered in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of negative prices in the game involves optimizing profit, which is a common theme in the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses the properties of different network topologies, which falls under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The analysis of the profit factor involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which is a topic covered in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of matroid followers, which is a topic covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
